  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 425°F (220°C).",
    "Season the lamb shoulder with salt, black pepper, cumin, coriander, thyme, and rosemary.",
    "Heat the olive oil in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat.",
    "Sear the lamb shoulder until browned on all sides, about 5 minutes.",
    "Transfer the lamb to a plate and set aside.",
    "Add the sliced onions to the pot and cook until caramelized, about 10 minutes.",
    "Add the sliced carrots and potatoes to the pot and cook for 5 minutes.",
    "Return the lamb shoulder to the pot and pour in the honey and smoked paprika.",
    "Mix well and transfer the pot to the preheated oven.",
    "Roast the lamb for 2-1/2 to 3 hours, or until the meat is tender and falls apart easily.",
    "Let the lamb rest for 10 minutes before slicing and serving.",
    "Garnish with fresh herbs, if desired.",
    "Serve with the roasted potatoes and carrots on the side.",
    "Optional: sprinkle with garlic powder and paprika for extra flavor."
  ],
